{"TopicId":153706,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Mod that changes m/s -\u0026gt; mph (miles per hour) and/or others?","CreatedByName":"Kerbal the Kerbal","CreatedById":171262,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T03:30:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal the Kerbal","CreatedById":171262,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T03:30:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI seriously need a mod that can change m/s to mph (miles per hour) and/or km/h (kilometers per hour)\u00A0so that I\u00A0can measure how fast my spaceplane can go. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;.;\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E\u00A0Is there any mod that can do so?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DD_bwest","CreatedById":164906,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T07:07:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni think there is a mod called speed unit changer that does it. but i dont know if its up to date.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nalternatively you just just multiply your m/s by 3.6 to get km/h\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T08:01:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E can do this...but it also changes the entire aerodynamics model. If you want better units for a spaceplane, you should rather change to Mach numbers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Magzimum","CreatedById":167187,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T08:21:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn behalf of the rest of the world I would like to leave this here: a map of all countries in the world that are still using the imperial units of measure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022MapOfCountriesNotMetric-800px.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://blogs.ascentutah.org/kdale/wp-content/uploads/sites/32/2014/09/MapOfCountriesNotMetric-800px.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T08:34:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022h5UsGxK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022440\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/h5UsGxK.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Champ","CreatedById":96425,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T09:49:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222893015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482136484\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/h5UsGxK.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022h5UsGxK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022440\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/h5UsGxK.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTotally wrong. Many countries landed on the moon. Soviets were the first to land on the moon. Chinese landed on the moon more recently. I think even the indian space program landed on the moon (or was it an impactor ?). By the way, i don\u0027t think using the imperial unit system helped in any way when the US did their manned landing on the moon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Palaceviking","CreatedById":166883,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T10:08:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet the flaming commence!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a lighter note.....why?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T10:25:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222893057\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482140993\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002296425\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Champ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, Champ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy the way, i don\u0027t think using the imperial unit system helped in any way when the US did their manned landing on the moon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, but it did help them get \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_Climate_Orbiter#Cause_of_failure\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ea hundred and sixty kilometres closer to Mars\u003C/a\u003E :v\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Magzimum","CreatedById":167187,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-19T10:28:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy intention of the previous post was to show that a lot of information (engineering, but also on space travel, and possibly on moon landings) is available in the metric system, simply because a large part of the world uses that as its system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-27T05:13:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222893006\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482135661\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167187\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Magzimum\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/19/2016 at 0:21 AM, Magzimum said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn behalf of the rest of the world I would like to leave this here: a map of all countries in the world that are still using the imperial units of measure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://blogs.ascentutah.org/kdale/wp-content/uploads/sites/32/2014/09/MapOfCountriesNotMetric-800px.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022MapOfCountriesNotMetric-800px.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://blogs.ascentutah.org/kdale/wp-content/uploads/sites/32/2014/09/MapOfCountriesNotMetric-800px.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote, however, that there are still other oddball units out there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe usual supermarket unit of measure in China is the jing (phonetic, I don\u0027t know how to spell it in Pinyin), equal to 500 grams.\u00A0 I think the stores are required to use the metric units but almost nothing is priced by the kg, rather by the 500g.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-27T08:04:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t resist..\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://lmgtfy.com/?q=1m%2Fs\u002Bto\u002Bmph\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://lmgtfy.com/?q=1m%2Fs\u002Bto\u002Bmph\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheKosmonaut","CreatedById":40652,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-12T13:53:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome politically charged\u00A0posts have been removed. Of all things you guys get your jimmies rustled over, it\u0027s units of measurement? No politics, people.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis thread is quite old and we don\u0027t need to be reviving it so we can talk about how our numbers are better than yours.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:36px;\u0022\u003ELocked\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}